In the wake of social media claims that Banda Homes, a real estate company is set to collapse after hoodwinking investors, the company has termed the claims insensitive, slanderous and malicious. Addressing journalists at the company’s housing estate at Kimunyu village on Kenyatta Road, Gatundu South, Kiambu county the company chief executive Fabian Nzivo said contrary to the allegations, their off-plan housing model has seen many Kenyans own  home. Nzivo said that they have reported the matter to the relevant authorities which are investigating the source of the claims before taking legal action. Nzivo reiterated that contrary to the their allegations, Oak Park Estate project, a development of 77 units at Kimunyu which was commissioned in march 2018 will be handed over in march this year as promised to clients.